author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Arrow jumps in season 4 premiere on Wednesday - Arrow Cult -
text: Arrow was up from 2014's premiere in its return to The CW on Wednesday (October 7), according to Nielsen figures.The DC Comics series jumped one-tenth of a point from last year to 1.1 (2.67m) at 8pm, followed by Supernatural earning 0.9 (1.94m) at 9pm. © The CW / Dean Buscher Fox dominated the key 18-49 demographic once again on Wednesday with 3.4.Empire slid four-tenths of a point to 5.1 (13.10m) at 9pm on Fox, after Rosewood's score of 1.8 (5.75m) at 8pm.CBS's Survivor hit 2.0 (9.07m) at 8pm, Criminal Minds fell to a low of 1.7 (9.08m) at 9pm and Code Black averaged 1.2 (6.83m) at 10pm.Three of ABC's comedies were down overall, with The Middle garnering 2.0 (7.30m) at 8pm, The Goldbergs interesting 2.1 (6.60m) at 8.30pm and Modern Family dropping three-tenths to 2.7 (7.99m) at 9pm. © ABC Black-ish actually rose to 1.9 (5.86m) at 9.30pm, while Nashville swiftly dipped to 1.0 (4.36m) at 10pm on ABC.The Mysteries of Laura attracted 1.1 (7.11m) at 8pm on NBC, before Law & Order: SVU hit 1.6 (7.00m) at 9pm and Chicago PD scored 1.5 (6.49m) at 10pm.
